1.词汇  电影词汇
soundtrack  电影配乐
stories 故事
characters  角色

[FELTON]    I don't agree. You know?
[FELTON]    I think a soundtrack is very important to a movie.
[FELTON]    Soundtracks aren't boring.
[FELTON]    OK, I agree that not all soundtracks are great.
[FELTON]    But movies like 'Jaws' and 'Superman' and 'Indiana Jones' 
            have some of the best action movie soundtracks of all time.
[FELTON]    I think it was genius to use classical music in the 
            science-fiction movie '2001: A Space Odyssey'.
[FELTON]    'Love Story' has one of the saddest soundtracks of all dramas.
[AN]        My favorite movies are westerns.
[AN]        The stories are good...
[AN]        ... the characters are grest, and there's just never a dull 
            and boring moment.

//  Harry Jenkins 是一位优秀的演员
Harry Jenkins is an excellent actor.    
//  Kate Ellis 是目前好莱坞最优秀的女演员
Kate Ellis is the best actress in Hollywood right now.  
//  Betty Bevis 在英国是大明星
Betty Bevis is a big star in the UK.
//  她在片中饰演一位极为有趣的角色
She plays one of the most interesting characters in the film.

//  Jenny Lindstorm 在她漫长的职业过程中拍摄了15部电影.
Jenny Lindstorm directed 15 movies during her long career. 
//  她是一位了不起的导演.
She was an incredible director.

//  Invasion of the Body Snatchers 的特效很差劲.
The special effects in 'Invasion of the Body Snatchers' are terrible.
//  我喜欢历史题材影片中的服装
I love the costumes in historical dramas.
//  恐怖片的情节荒谬可笑
The plot of that horror movie are ridiculous.
//  我非常喜欢'Casablanca'的原生音乐
I love the soundtrack of 'Casablanca'.

2.表达  'one of the' 和 'some of the'
some of the best    //  最好的其中一些
of all time         //  总是
one of the saddest  //  最悲哀的其中之一
of all dramas       //  在所有的戏剧中

用one of the + 最高级 + 复数名词表达某物是某一组的一部分,是无法超越的.
//  'The Birds'里有我见过的最令人振奋的情节之一.
'The Birds' has one of the most exciting plots I've ever seen.
用some of the + 最高级 +复数名词来表达未被超过得一组中的两个或更多个东西.
//  'Avatar'有一些前所未有最好的特殊效果
'Avatar' has some of the best special effects ever.
您可以用诸如 of all time 和 ever 的表达来加重强调.
//  Amelie是有史以来最伟大的人物之一.
Amelie is one of the greatest characters of all time.
//  'The Terminator'是有史以来最酷的电影之一.
'The Terminator' is one of the coolest movies ever.

3.表达  询问和描述电影
//  最好的动作影片配乐中的其中一些
some of the best action movie soundtracks
//  我想......更明智
I think it was genius to ...
//  "爱情故事"有所有戏剧中最伤心的配乐中的其中一个
'Love Story' has one of the saddest soundtracks of all dramas.
//  故事都很不错
The stories are good.
//  这些角色都挺棒.
The characters are great.
//  从没有枯燥乏味的时刻
There's just never a dull or boring moment.

以下是一些你可以询问影片的常见问题.注意,movie和film所指相同,但film更正式一点.
A:  What did you think of the film?     //  你觉得这部影片怎么样?
B:  I loved it!                         //  我非常喜欢

A:  How did you like it?                //  你喜欢它吗?
B:  I didn't like it at all.            //  我一点也不喜欢.

A:  How would you describe it?          //  你要怎么形容他?
B:  It's a romantic comedy.             //  这是一部浪漫喜剧.

A:  What's your favorite movie?         //  你最喜欢哪部电影?
B:  My favorite movie is 'Chinatown'.   //  我最喜欢的电影是'Chinatown'

你可以用短语 all-time favorite ,谈论你最爱的电影.
//  我最喜欢的电影是'Casablanca'
My all-time favorite movie is 'Casablanca'.

使用以下问题,询问电影的细节.
A:  What's it about?                    //  它是关于什么的?
B:  It's about a boy and his dog.       //  它是关于一个男孩和他的狗的故事.

A:  Whos directed it?                   //  谁导演的?
B:  It was directed by Woody Allen.     //  由 Woody Allen 导演.

A:  Who's in it?                        //  里面有谁?
B:  It stars Glenda Smith.              //  主演是 Glenda Smith.

A:  How's the acting?                   //  演技怎么样?
B:  It's really good.                   //  演技非常不错.

A:  Where does the film take place?     //  电影在哪发生?
B:  It takes place in Paris in 1952.    //  发生在1952年的巴黎.

A:  How does it end?                    //  电影是怎么样结尾的?
B:  Sheila and Mark get married.        //  Sheila 和 Mark 结婚了.